A man has been charged with driving offences in connection with the death of a father who was found on the side of a road in Leicestershire. Tommy Hunter, from Newhall in Derbyshire, was discovered dead in Ashby on 11 December after he failed to return from a night out.Brandon Beesla, 27, of Hillsdale Road in Burton-upon-Trent, Staffordshire, has been charged with failing to stop after a road accident and driving a motor vehicle in a condition likely to cause danger of injury. He is due to appear at Leicester Magistrates' Court on Friday. 
Mr Hunter, 27, had been reported missing after not returning home from a nightclub. His body was found in hedges off Burton Road the following morning. Leicestershire Police said an investigation into the circumstances surrounding Mr Hunter's death was ongoing. Follow BBC Leicester on Facebook, on X, or on Instagram. Send your story ideas to eastmidsnews@bbc.co.uk or via WhatsApp on 0808 100 2210.
